# {{ project_name }}

> {{ project_description }}

Generated from [OpenProductKit](https://github.com/ravipurohit1991/OpenProductKit) — a white-label product-template built around **one decoupled core** with thin web / CLI / desktop adapters.

## Architecture

```
packages/core        Pure Python domain models + Repository ports. No FastAPI, no DB, no HTTP.
packages/plugin-api  Extension SDK: the Plugin contract + registry. No runtime deps.
packages/licensing   Entitlement: dev stub, Ed25519 signed offline tokens, file/HTTP providers.
apps/backend         FastAPI adapter. Owns SQLModel persistence (implements core ports).
apps/cli             Typer CLI + task runner ({{ cli_name }}).
apps/frontend        React + Vite web UI. Talks to the backend over HTTP - or the desktop bridge.
{%- if desktop_framework == 'pywebview' %}
apps/desktop         pywebview shell: the same UI + core in one process. No sidecar, no port.
{%- elif desktop_framework == 'electron' %}
apps/desktop-electron  Electron shell over a sidecar backend on localhost (one origin, no CORS).
{%- elif desktop_framework == 'tauri' %}
apps/desktop-tauri   Tauri (Rust) shell over a sidecar backend on localhost (one origin, no CORS).
{%- endif %}
extensions/          Example plugins (basic, cli, paid, and the on-demand marketplace demo).
marketplace/         catalog.json — what the Marketplace tab offers beyond installed plugins.
```

Business logic lives only in `packages/core`. Everything else is a delivery mechanism.

## The demo: a small Resource Vault (replace it!)

Projects group notes; notes carry tags; you can search notes by project, tag or
free text. The same core services power the web API, the CLI and the desktop
app.

The demo is a worked example, not the product — every demo line is fenced with
a `[demo]` marker (`grep -rn "\[demo\]" packages apps` lists them all), and
**[AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)** contains the layer-by-layer recipe for replacing it
with your own domain. Working with an AI coding agent (Claude Code, Cursor,
Codex, …)? It reads `AGENTS.md` automatically — *"replace the demo with
&lt;your idea&gt;"* is a reasonable first prompt.

```bash
# via the CLI adapter
uv run {{ cli_name }} project add "Research"
uv run {{ cli_name }} project list
uv run {{ cli_name }} note add <project-id> "Read paper" --tag ml --tag todo
uv run {{ cli_name }} note list --q paper
```

```
GET/POST /api/projects            list / create projects
GET      /api/projects/{id}       fetch a project
GET/POST /api/notes               search (?project_id=&tag=&q=) / create
GET      /api/notes/{id}          fetch a note
```

## Plugins / extensions

Plugins are ordinary Python packages that advertise a `Plugin` through the
`{{ pkg_slug }}.plugins` entry-point group. The host discovers them with
`importlib.metadata` — a **dev-time** model (no arbitrary runtime code loading;
end-user/runtime install is a roadmap item). A plugin can contribute backend
routes, CLI commands, a settings schema, admin nav items and a health check, and
may declare a `required_plan` that the license provider gates on.

Three examples live in `extensions/`: `basic` (a backend route), `cli` (adds
`{{ cli_name }} example-cli`), and `paid` (license-gated analytics, needs the `pro`
plan). Manage them from the CLI or the **Plugins** tab in the web UI:

```bash
uv run {{ cli_name }} plugin list
uv run {{ cli_name }} plugin disable example.basic
uv run {{ cli_name }} plugin enable example.basic
uv run {{ cli_name }} example-cli greet Ada        # command from the cli plugin
```

```
GET  /api/plugins                 list installed plugins + state
POST /api/plugins/{id}/enable     enable a plugin
POST /api/plugins/{id}/disable    disable a plugin
```

## Marketplace

The **Marketplace** tab merges installed plugins with `marketplace/catalog.json`
(or a hosted catalog via `APP_MARKETPLACE_URL`): users see what exists, what is
locked behind a plan, and how to install what's missing. Pasting a signed
license token in the tab unlocks paid extensions **immediately** — plugin
routes are license-checked per-request, no restart.

Try the full loop: `extensions/example-marketplace-plugin` ships in the repo
but is not installed until you run the command the tab shows
(`uv add {{ pkg_slug }}-plugin-reports`); it then stays locked until a `pro`
token is activated.

```bash
uv run {{ cli_name }} marketplace list             # same view, headless
uv run {{ cli_name }} marketplace unlock <token>   # activate a license token
```

```
GET  /api/marketplace             installed + catalog, with lock state
POST /api/marketplace/unlock      verify + persist a license token, apply now
```

