## Desktop app (pywebview — no HTTP server)

The same UI in a native window; API calls cross a JS bridge into the FastAPI
app **in the same process** — no sidecar, no port. Data lives in your OS
app-data directory.

```bash
uv run {{ cli_name }} build web       # build the UI once (and after UI changes)
uv run {{ cli_name }} desktop         # native window, dev mode
uv run {{ cli_name }} desktop --check # headless smoke test
uv run {{ cli_name }} build desktop   # PyInstaller onedir bundle into ./dist
```

Code signing / notarization is intentionally left to you (per-vendor
certificates); expect OS warnings on unsigned builds.
{%- elif desktop_framework == 'electron' %}
## Desktop app (Electron + sidecar backend)

The Electron shell spawns the backend on a free localhost port (it serves the
API *and* the built web UI — one origin, no CORS) and opens a window on it.
Data lives in your OS app-data directory.

```bash
uv run {{ cli_name }} build web       # build the UI once (and after UI changes)
pnpm install                    # once — installs Electron
uv run {{ cli_name }} desktop         # native window, dev mode
uv run {{ cli_name }} desktop --check # headless smoke test of the sidecar
uv run {{ cli_name }} build desktop   # PyInstaller sidecar + electron-builder → dist/electron
```

Code signing / notarization is intentionally left to you (per-vendor
certificates); expect OS warnings on unsigned builds.
{%- elif desktop_framework == 'tauri' %}
## Desktop app (Tauri + sidecar backend)

The Tauri (Rust) shell spawns the backend on a free localhost port (it serves
the API *and* the built web UI — one origin, no CORS) and opens a window on it.
Data lives in your OS app-data directory. Requires the
[Rust toolchain](https://rustup.rs).

```bash
uv run {{ cli_name }} build web       # build the UI once (and after UI changes)
pnpm install                    # once — installs the Tauri CLI
uv run {{ cli_name }} desktop         # native window, dev mode (compiles the shell first time)
uv run {{ cli_name }} desktop --check # headless smoke test of the sidecar
uv run {{ cli_name }} build desktop   # PyInstaller sidecar + tauri build
```

Replace the placeholder icons before shipping:
`pnpm -C apps/desktop-tauri tauri icon your-icon.png`. Code signing /
notarization is intentionally left to you (per-vendor certificates); expect OS
warnings on unsigned builds.
{%- endif %}
