## Licensing

Development uses a stub that grants the `pro` plan (set `APP_LICENSE_DEV_PLAN`
to try other tiers). For real installs, issue Ed25519-signed offline tokens:

```bash
uv run {{ cli_name }} license keygen                            # vendor: once; prints APP_LICENSE_PUBLIC_KEY
uv run {{ cli_name }} license issue --licensee "Acme" --plan pro --days 365   # vendor: per customer
uv run {{ cli_name }} license install LIC1....                  # customer: activate
uv run {{ cli_name }} license status                            # inspect the resolved license
```

Gate a route with `Depends(require_plan("pro"))` or
`Depends(require_feature("reports"))`; gate UI with `useEntitlement()` and
`<LockedFeatureCard/>`. See the License tab in the web UI, and the gated
"Export vault" demo. An HTTP license-server provider is included as well
(`APP_LICENSE_URL`).

## Typed API client (generated)

The web UI never hand-writes API types. `apps/frontend/src/client/schema.d.ts`
is generated from the backend's OpenAPI schema; `openapi-fetch` makes every
request path, parameter, body and response type-safe. Regenerate after changing
the API:

```bash
uv run {{ cli_name }} gen            # dump OpenAPI + regenerate src/client/schema.d.ts
```

Change an endpoint and forget to update a call site, and the TypeScript build
fails — drift is caught by the compiler.

## Database migrations

Alembic is the single source of truth for the schema (migrations are applied
automatically on app startup, so dev and tests are zero-config).

```bash
uv run {{ cli_name }} db migrate                 # apply pending migrations
uv run {{ cli_name }} db revision -m "add x"     # autogenerate a migration from model changes
uv run {{ cli_name }} db downgrade               # revert one step
uv run {{ cli_name }} db reset                   # drop everything and re-apply
```

